.TH _PRINTF 3 "2025" "Holberton School" "Library Functions Manual"

.SH NAME
_printf \- custom formatted output conversion

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.PP
.BI "int _printf(const char *" format ", ...);"

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf()
function produces output according to a format string.
It writes output to stdout, the standard output stream.

.PP
The format string is composed of zero or more directives.
Each directive is either a literal character or a conversion specifier.

.SH CONVERSION SPECIFIERS
.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.

.TP
.B %s
Prints a string of characters.
If the argument is NULL, prints (null).

.TP
.B %d
Prints a decimal integer.

.TP
.B %i
Prints an integer.

.TP
.B %%
Prints a literal percent sign.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the number of characters printed (excluding the null byte).
Returns \-1 if the format string is NULL.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Print a simple string:
.PP
.RS
_printf("Hello, World!\n");
.RE
.PP
Print a character:
.PP
.RS
_printf("%c", 'A');
.RE
.PP
Print an integer:
.PP
.RS
_printf("%d", 42);
.RE

